      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the pedicle screw–rod–block assembly. Stiffness QoI changes 1.3% between medium (element edge ~0.4 mm) and fine (element edge ~0.2 mm) meshes. Medium mesh adopted for ensemble runs to balance accuracy and compute cost."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals converge below 1e-5 for all load steps; energy balance checked.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson iterations converged to force residual < 5e-6 for all 11 simulation runs. Energy balance confirmed within 0.1%. No spurious hourglassing or contact chattering detected in post-processing."
